\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 C1 should be working hard on their \cb5 external goals\cb1  but they should also be spending time with C2 in a way that makes your readers \cb5 see why these two people really belong together\cb1 . (If you\'92re writing from both characters\'92 POV, the same goes for C2 and their goals.) Their feelings will also go from \cb5 initial attraction to deeper feelings\cb1  even when they\'92re still resisting each other. When they look back on this time later on, they should realise how they were better people when they were with each other. \cb5 Because they\'92re going to have such big problems later in the story, you need to set up their love story the right way - it needs to make sense they finally decide to give their relationship a chance despite everything.
\fs24 \cb1 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 You should remember that your characters are still 
